section.guidelines-contents.contents
  h1 Ruby Kaja 2012 Selection Criteria
  h2 Kaja are chosen by the community
  p Every active Ruby Community may select one Kaja.
  p The method for choosing a Kaja itself is up to the community. The Kaja need not be a member of the community itself.
  h2 Selection Schedule
  h3 Participation Application (June to July)
  dd Communities who wish to select a Kaja apply via the registration form.
  h3 Descision and publication of participating communities (Beginning of August)
  dd Organizers will review the applications and publish the participating communities on this site.
  h3 Registration of Ruby Kaja (mid-August)
  dd Each participating community will be able to register one Kaja from a special form.
  h3 Announcement (mid-September)
  dd
    |  "Ruby Kaja" will be announced on this site in mid-September.
    br
    |  We plan to have a ceremony recognizing the first generation of Ruby Kaja at Sapporo Ruby Kaigi 2012.
  h2 Participation Qualifications
  p
    |  At the time of application, the community actively conducts official activities.
    br
    |  (An active community has at least three members and has a public record of activity over the last three months. The management committee will review each application.) 
  h2 Participation Procedure
  p  Communities who wish to select a Ruby Kaja should fill in the application form within the application period. Please note that the management committee reserve the right to reject applications if they feel they don't match the spirt of Ruby Kaja. 
